		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Jeroen,<br /><br />Concerning the other issue I was having with the playfield being written incorrectly. I tried resenting the scroll as you suggested after doing all the PPU writes for the playfield background but I'm still having the same issue.<br /><br />I think the problem maybe scroll timing versus a comparison check that I'm doing. Example In this code: <div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; ;; Load In Title Screen<br />&nbsp; ;;Start Scrolling For Title Screen<br />&nbsp; ;;Check if Scrolling is done for title screen<br />&nbsp; LDA gamestate<br />&nbsp; CMP #$01<br />&nbsp; BEQ TitleScrollFinished<br />&nbsp; LDA scroll<br />&nbsp; CMP #$FF<br />&nbsp; BEQ TitleScrollFinished</div><br /><br />I'm checking if the start button has been pressed to exit the title screen and go into a different &quot;gamestate&quot; which would be the game play field at this point. Is it possible that it could be a timing issue? Like perhaps the screen is still scrolled for at least 8 pixels before the processor realizes the start button has been pressed via the compare? Right below the compare is a check to see if the title screen has scroll 255 pixels, at which point it stops scrolling. Logically to me, this should negate the over scroll issue that I think it might be, but I'm not sure.<br /><br />Any thoughts?

		

